<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL: RAMS 14, ARIZONA CARDINALS 12; IT'S A GRIPPING VICTORY FOR THE 
RAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By T.J. SIMERS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Ram Review 
</P>
<P>
 First Quarter: The pageantry of opening day, sky divers, balloons and 
first-round pick Wayne Gandy always knew one day he would be sitting on the 
bench for an NFL game . . . Phoenix brings 600-plus fans, thus outnumbering Ram 
fans two-to-one . . . Elapsed time of national anthem is 1 minute 26 seconds -- 
18 seconds shy of equaling Rams' longest offensive drive . . . Keith Loneker 
starts with Jackie Slater and you thought you'd seen it all when Lisa Marie 
Presley and Michael Jackson got together . . . Jerome Bettis offers 
touching-fumbling tribute to recuperating Cleveland Gary . . . Ram defense 
tough, Jimmie Jones penetrates, Joe Kelly forces fumble, Todd Lyght goes 74 
yards for TD and Gandy is permitted off bench to join celebration . . . Rams 7, 
Cardinals 0. 
</P>
<P>
 Second Quarter: Fifteen minutes into season and Chris Miller is still standing 
. . . Twenty-nine minutes into season and Rams are still looking for their 
initial first down . . . Defensive end Brad Ottis is spotted on field; do Rams 
realize this game counts? Lyght gets beat in end zone, recovers to knock down 
pass, and good thing Steve Beuerlein couldn't hit Pacific if standing on edge 
of Santa Monica Pier . . . Five minutes until halftime when Chinese Acrobats 
perform and Gandy wants to know if he can watch? Rams get first down with 28 
seconds left in half because Eric Swann steps offside; ball will be on display 
in Orange County Hall of Fame . . . Rams 7, Cardinals 6. 
</P>
<P>
 Third Quarter: Bettis starts quarter averaging 2.6 yards a carry, and at this 
rate he will have to carry the ball 769 times to reach 2,000 yards . . . 
Marquez Pope interception leads to Bettis TD and Chuck Knox is asking for raise 
instead of expecting pink slip . . . Rookie Toby Wright has more hits in debut 
than Bruce Willis has in whole career . . . Rams are going to win, Rams are 
going to win, and Georgia Frontiere is seen kissing Forrest Gump on the cheek . 
. . Arizona scores, fails on two-point conversion and so that's Buddy Ball . . 
. Flipper Anderson goes deep, makes circus catch and somewhere in New Orleans 
on Sunday night Jim Everett was talking to himself.Rams 14, Cardinals 12. 
</P>
