David Rocker gets a sack, yeah sure, and Madonna enters the convent, Don King 
takes a vow of silence . . . Keith Lyle has an interception, Robert Young 
applies pressure and it's like the media has been saying all along: These guys 
are really good . . . Johnny Bailey tries to catch a punt with his facemask, 
Ricky Proehl has Steve Israel beat deep for game-winning touchdown, Chris 
Miller stumbles and fumbles, Cards don't take advantage and later Leigh 
Steinberg takes credit for Saving the Rams . . . Bettis game of keepaway drops 
Ram magic number to 15 to secure playoff berth. Rams 14, Cardinals 12. 
</P>
