MAN, 86, STUNG 1,000 TIMES IN BEE SWARM; 3 OTHERS ALSO STUNG 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bees stung an 86-year-old man more than 1,000 times Saturday and attacked 
three other people after the man disturbed a 10-foot-tall hive as he mowed his 
lawn. 
</P>
<P>
 J. C. Johnson, his son, a police officer and an emergency worker were taken to 
the hospital.Police quarantined a 10-block area while beekeepers destroyed the 
hive. 
</P>
<P>
 The bees attacked Johnson and then stung his 59-year-old son about 500 times 
as he tried to help his father. Both were in stable condition Sunday at a 
hospital. 
</P>
