<HEADLINE>
<P>
PRO FOOTBALL; FAN FROM IRVINE ARRESTED AT GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A fan from Irvine raced onto the field during Sunday's Pittsburgh-Dallas game 
and eluded several police officers during a broken-field chase before being 
handcuffed and arrested. 
</P>
<P>
 William Thompson, 22, was charged with defiant trespass and disorderly 
conduct, according to Pittsburgh police. He was being held Sunday night in the 
downtown city jail. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
