<HEADLINE>
<P>
KINGS GET TENTATIVE DEAL WITH FREE AGENT BLAKE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Rob Blake, the Kings' free-agent defenseman, reached a tentative agreement 
Sunday on a four-year deal, which is subject to league approval over contract 
language. Blake's agent, Ron Salcer, said the defenseman probably would not 
start practicing with the Kings until the deal is cleared.The team's first 
training camp practice at Iceoplex in North Hills is today. 
</P>
<P>
 Those expected in camp include newcomers Rick Tocchet, Rob Brown, Dan Quinn, 
Matt Johnson, Yanic Perreault, Sean O'Donnell and Michel Petit. Perhaps the 
most intriguing addition is 18-year-old goaltender Jamie Storr, the Kings' 
first-round draft pick (seventh overall) in June. Storr has a chance to make 
the team. 
</P>
<P>
 "He's the best junior goalie I've seen at that level and that includes pretty 
good goalies," Kings General Manager Sam McMaster said. "Don Beaupre played 
with Minnesota as an underage junior, and I think he (Storr) is more prepared 
than Don was at that time and more prepared than (Tom) Barrasso." LISA DILLMAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
