DEATH OF WOMAN INVESTIGATED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County homicide detectives are investigating the death of an 
elderly Lake Los Angeles woman whose charred body was found in the debris of a 
garage fire, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Firefighters found the body of the unidentified 87-year-old woman after they 
extinguished the blaze in the 10300 block of Avenue R-14, near 105th Street 
East, said Diana Aronson, a dispatcher for the Los Angeles County Fire 
Department. 
</P>
