<HEADLINE>
<P>
PIPE BOMB FOUND ON GARDEN GROVE FREEWAY DEFUSED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A small pipe bomb found on the shoulder of the westbound Garden Grove Freeway 
was safely removed and defused by the Orange County Sheriff's bomb squad Sunday 
morning, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The westbound lanes between Euclid and Brookhurst streets were closed for an 
hour and 10 minutes after a California Department of Transportation cleanup 
crew found the device at 10:09 a.m., a California Highway Patrol dispatcher 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 One end of the 1-by-6-inch device appeared to have a fuse that had been 
burned, but it didn't detonate, said Orange County Sheriff's Lt. Bill Leonard. 
</P>
<P>
 It was not known how the device came to be placed on the freeway shoulder. 
</P>
