<HEADLINE>
<P>
PACIFIC WATCH: JAPAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Domestic Auto Sales Increase: The Japan Automobile Dealers Assn. said domestic 
vehicle sales rose 12% in August from a year earlier to 295,283, the third 
straight month of gains and the first double-digit gain in four years."Domestic 
vehicle sales have entered a real recovery phase. Consumers have begun to buy 
new cars" to replace cars bought during the economic boom of the late 1980s, 
said Hiroshi Suemasa, a senior analyst at Kankaku Research Institute Inc. 
August sales of imported vehicles soared 70.3% from a year earlier to 23,391, 
the 10th straight month of rises, JADA said. Sales of Ford Motor Co. cars 
rocketed 200% from a year earlier, industry sources said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
